    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Incubation period: 7-14 days",
      "subsections": {
        "Symptoms": {
          "text": "Variable and non-specific\nOften presents as acute, self-limited illness, with no complications\n[1]\nMost Common Symptoms\nHigh\nfever\nCan last ~1 week\nRash\nMacular or maculopapular, blanching, non-pruritic\nStarts centrally and moves to the extremities\nCan involve palms/soles but usually sparing\nStarts 6-7 days after symptom onset (fever onset)\nHeadache\nArthralgias\nOther Symptoms/Complications\nHepatomegaly\nSplenomegaly\nCough\nDiarrhea\nNausea/Vomiting\nAbdominal pain\nMeningitis\nConfusion\nEndocarditis\nRarely\ndeath\n(<1% of cases)",
          "tables": []
        }
